						Cu[m] his etiam Salium, apophthegmatum, epigrammatum, gnomaru[m],
						regularu[m] ( delitijs.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				The daily sustenance of divine actualization and irony. And with these, the delights found in witticisms, aphorisms,
				epigrams, maxims, and principles.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
